Ask HN: Friendly Fraud / Chargeback Abuse
text: If you're a small business owner or run a SaaS product with a small team, how do you handle customers doing chargebacks? It's expensive to dispute each charge, some processors are biased against you, and you end up losing often. So you lose money on the product / service delivered, get hit with fees, and are emotionally drained and worn down.

Ask HN: Why Do Some CS Researchers Switch to Software Engineering Careers
text: I've been noticing a trend for the past five years, where people (often with PhDs) who start their careers working as researchers for industrial research labs (e.g., IBM Almaden Research Center, HP Labs, Intel Research, etc.) end up switching careers and become software engineers.  I'm curious about whether the trend is due to personal interests (e.g., wanting to create production-quality software instead of research prototypes, wanting to avoid "publish-or-perish" pressures, higher salaries offered for SE positions) or due to other reasons (I have noticed a gradual winding down of industrial research labs in the past decade).  I currently work at an industrial research lab.  I enjoy doing research but I'm concerned about my ability to remain a researcher during my career.
